results.name: Number of chains of factorizations of n into factors > 1, ordered by refinement, starting with the prime factorization of n and ending with the maximum factorization (n).
comment: If x and y are factorizations of the same integer and it is possible to produce x by further factoring the factors of y, flattening, and sorting, then x <= y.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Jul 23 2018
